What is Bluetooth?
Bluetooth is a wireless technology standard for exchanging data over short distances (using short-wavelength UHF radio waves in the ISM band from 2.4 to 2.485 GHz[4]) from fixed and mobile devices, and building personal area networks (PANs).

Yesterday, you should have written a journal describing how a network was compromised and how you solved the crime. 

Did you mention Bluetooth? 
No

Why or why not?
The susspect used a infected USB drive to bypass the router filter.

      What do the following tools do? And what is a sample command for each?
    1.hciconfig
	hciconfig is used to configure bluetooth devices
    2.hcitool
	hcitool is used to configure bluetooth connections and send some special command to bluetooth devices.
    3.hcidump
	hcidump reads raw HCI data coming from and going to a bluetooth device and prints to the screen commands, events and data in human-readable form
Run apt-cache search bluetooth |less - What are three interesting packages you see? How are they interesting?
bluelog, amora-applet, blueman
